{"id":"revelation-of-christ","term":"Revelation of Christ","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The second advent of Christ. Three different Greek words are used by the apostles to express this, (1) apokalupsis (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 1:1\">1 Cor. 1</a>;<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 7:1\">7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Thessalonians 1:7\">2 Thess. 1:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 1:7\">1 Pet. 1:7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Peter 1:13\">13</a>); (2) parousia (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 24:3\">Matt. 24:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 24:27\">27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Thessalonians 2:19\">1 Thess. 2:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 5:7\">James 5:7</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"James 5:8\">8</a>); (3) epiphaneia (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 6:14\">1 Tim. 6:14</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Timothy 1:10\">2 Tim. 1:10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Timothy 4:1\">4:1-8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Titus 2:13\">Titus 2:13</a>). There existed among Christians a wide expectation, founded on <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 24:29\">Matt. 24:29</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 24:30\">30</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Matthew 24:34\">34</a>, of the speedy return of Christ. (See MILLENNIUM.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Corinthians 1:1","1 Corinthians 7:1","2 Thessalonians 1:7","1 Peter 1:7","1 Peter 1:13","Matthew 24:3","Matthew 24:27","1 Thessalonians 2:19","James 5:7","James 5:8","1 Timothy 6:14","2 Timothy 1:10","2 Timothy 4:1","Titus 2:13","Matthew 24:29","Matthew 24:30","Matthew 24:34"]}